## Betting Strategy Rules (Refined from Backtests)

### Recommended Bankroll Allocation
| Bet Type | Allocation | Reasoning |
|----------|------------|-----------|
| WIN (favorites) | 45% | High strike rate with elite jockeys |
| PLACE (value) | 25% | Consistent returns, 70%+ hit rate |
| QUINELLA | 20% | Outsized returns when hit |
| RESERVE | 10% | For Group 1 / feature races |

### WIN Bet Rules
- Back horses in odds range **2.0-7.0** with elite jockeys
- Heavier stake on short favorites (<3.0) at **Sha Tin only**
- **Avoid** short favorites at Happy Valley
- Skip races with no clear form standout

### PLACE Bet Rules
- Target value picks in **5.0-15.0** odds range
- Focus on consistent jockeys with high place %
- Expected hit rate: **70%+**
- Steady profit driver

### QUINELLA Bet Rules
- Back top 2 in market as default
- At Happy Valley: **Box 3-4 horses** (more upsets)
- Key profit driver - **700%+ ROI** in backtests
- Accept lower hit rate (~40%) for larger payouts

### Stake Sizing
- Use Kelly Criterion with fractional Kelly (25-50%)
- Maximum 5% bankroll per single bet
- Maximum 10% bankroll per race
- **Reduce all stakes by 30% at Happy Valley**

### Risk Management
- Track all bets and results
- Regular model calibration via Brier Score
- Pass on races with no value identified
- **Never chase losses** - stick to system

## Scraping Guidelines

### Rate Limiting
- Maximum 20 requests per minute to HKJC
- Use delays between requests
- Cache data when possible

### Error Handling
- **THROW ERRORS** for critical parsing failures (going, class, odds)
- **LOG WARNINGS** for non-critical fallbacks (surface, prize money)
- Never silently use default values for analytical data
- All errors must be visible in output

### Data Validation
- Validate all scraped data with Zod schemas
- Reject races with missing going/class/finish data
- Log all validation failures for review

## Backtest Guidelines

### Minimum Requirements
- At least **5 meetings** for meaningful analysis
- Mix of Sha Tin and Happy Valley
- Include different day types (weekend vs mid-week)

### Metrics to Track
| Metric | Target | Concern Level |
|--------|--------|---------------|
| WIN Strike Rate | >50% | <40% review strategy |
| PLACE Strike Rate | >70% | <60% review selections |
| Overall ROI | >100% | <50% pause betting |
| QNL Hit Rate | >35% | <25% widen coverage |

### Variance Expectations
- Single meeting: **-50% to +500%** swing normal
- 5 meetings: **+100% to +300%** expected range
- Best day may be **10x** worst day

## Analysis Best Practices

### Speed Ratings
- Adjust for class, going, weight
- Use par times for each track/distance combination
- Weight recent performances higher

### Form Analysis
- Recent form weighted more heavily (exponential decay)
- Consider quality of opposition
- Account for class changes
- **Days since last race**: Optimal 14-35 days

### Simulation
- Minimum 10,000 Monte Carlo iterations
- Include performance variance
- Track confidence intervals

## Testing Guidelines

### Unit Tests
- Test all calculation functions
- Mock scraped data for deterministic tests
- Test edge cases (empty arrays, zero values)

### Integration Tests
- Test full analysis pipeline with sample data
- Verify recommendation output format
- Test error handling scenarios

### Backtest Validation
- Run against known historical data
- Compare predictions vs actual results
- Calculate Brier Score for probability accuracy

## Git Commit Messages

Use conventional commits:
- `feat:` New feature
- `fix:` Bug fix
- `refactor:` Code refactoring
- `docs:` Documentation
- `test:` Tests
- `chore:` Maintenance

Example: `feat: add draw bias calculation for Happy Valley`
